description.narrative: The objective of the Rural Development Support Project (RDSP) is to increase incomes and reduce poverty in rural areas, while preserving the natural resource base. The project is part of the Rural Development Action Plan (Plan d'Action pour le Développement Rural - PADR), a broad-based program approved by the Government in 1999 to promote sustainable growth in agricultural production, foster food security and enhance access to basic services in the rural areas. The project would support demand-driven activities in agricultural production and technology transfer, and strengthen capacity at national, regional and community levels.
